#1: Marc could see how the SQL was laid out, that is where the Grouped By and things are in relation to WHERE #2: When there are no conditionals, I find it is nice in code to put a placeholder for future reference, I don't have to re-read a complex query to find the play I would put a conditional.
Anyways, it's all personal preference on queries this simple.

Nice I have to agree with Mike Rundle and here's an example:

